title: Sengiggi
description: Our first stop in Lombok was Sengiggi where we were lucky enough to catch the annual "Festival Sengiggi" - a celebration of traditional costumes and dances.

title: Kuta Lombok
description: Kuta is a small laid back surf town on the south coast of Lombok surrounded by some of the most beautiful bays and beaches in Indonesia.

title: Rinjani
description: At 3,726 meters high, Rinjani towers over the island of Lombok, Indonesia. For some crazy reason we decided to celebrate Kelvin's birthday by spending three days and two nights climbing it!

title: Gili Islands
description: After climbing a volcano some serious relaxation was called for and the Gili Islands were just the place...

title: Bali - Tianyar & Sidemen
description: Two weeks teaching English at Yayasan Widya Sari in northern Bali and a weekend trip to Sidemen

title: Bali - Ubud & the Bukit Peninsula
description: Monkeys and dance in Ubud, the incredible surf of the Bukit Peninsula and a visit to the bamboo buildings of the green school.

title: Australia - The Top End
description: In the first fortnight in Australia we saw crocodiles, waterfalls, sunsets, gorges, termite mounds and desert roads in "the top end".

title: Australia - The North West
description: We crossed over the border into Western Australia and visited Lake Argyll - the campsite with an amazing infinity pool. Then on to Broome then Karijini National Park...

title: Australia - The West Coast
description: From Exmouth down to Perth - sand, sun and surf!

title: Back to Lombok
description: A quick trip back to Lombok to refresh our Australian visas.

title: Australia - The South West
description: Cafe culture and skyscrapers in Perth, surf and vineyards in Margaret River, a terrifying climb up a 70 meter tree and then more surf in Denmark!

title: Fiji
description: A week in paradise. In cyclone season!

title: Kaikoura
description:
More stunning NZ landscapes... Mountains right down to the sea!

And **swimming with dolphins**!

title: Wellington & Taranaki
description: We passed back through Wellington and caught the start of the rugby sevens and then headed up to the Taranaki Peninsula to see the surf, the mountain and the clouds.

title: The Tongariro Crossing
description: The Tongariro Crossing is said by many to be the best day walk in NZ and maybe even the world... 20 kilometers across a crazy moonscape between volcanoes and lakes. And a side trip up Mount Doom aka Mount Ngauruhoe!
